manufacturerProductDescription.media_text: Supplementing with Vitamin C: Vitamin C, also known as Ascorbic Acid, is an essential nutrient naturally found in citrus fruits like oranges, grapefruit, and strawberries. It’s also featured in various supplement forms such as, capsules, liquid, gummies, bulk powder and pills. High Strength Formula: At Carlyle, our High Strength Vitamin C supplement is fortified with 1,000 mg of this essential nutrient per capsule, which is 2,222% of your daily value! It’s scientifically crafted with Rose Hips and is naturally gluten free and non-GMO with no artificial flavor or preservatives. Carlyle Vitamin C—Rooted In Wellness: Our expertise in sourcing the purest ingredients combined with advanced technologies makes us proud to deliver premium, honest supplements at the best value. Our high-quality Vitamin C is a testament to our commitment to excellence, made with powerful ingredients rooted in wellness. Thanks for choosing us in your pursuit to well living!

Statements regarding dietary supplements have not been evaluated by the FDA and are not intended to diagnose, treat, cure, or prevent any disease or health condition. Store in a cool, dry place.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 11, 2024
reviews.reviewText: I love the value and ability to consistency take vitamin c without constantly having to order another one. You know how everything on Amazon looks the same size in the picture? I was SHOCKED how big the box this came in was. Then I opened it.It is a HUGE bottle (300ct)!! It looks exactly the same as the smaller size just much bigger. It is a value and I love it. The trade off is the tablet is not coated so it is harder to swallow than other supplements I take even though it is not the largest. I still give a perfect score because value was my choice.

reviews.reviewText: First off this bottle is enormous so for the quality and price the value is incredible. Two...the quality is great. I have been taking vitamin c with rose hips my entire life. reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 3, 2023
reviews.reviewText: I got these as a supplement for my husband bc my Dr said almost everyone is at least a little low on D3 and when your low, you can't absorb other nutrients or even meds like your suppose to. I use the higher dose of the same brand bc I was pretty low. It brought mine from low safely into the normal range at my next labs (3 mo apart). He hadn't really thought about it until I asked for this review and we both noticed he has been feeling better overall. He says he doesn't notice any weird smell or taste and every once in a while he shakes the bottle bc they kind of clump together but then they're fine. They are smooth and easy to swallow. For the price and convenience I think the quality is good and I will buy again for both dosages. I hope this helps.
